eu.cqse.check.framework.preprocessor.c.new_c_preprocessor

Class PreprocessorConditionalTokenReplacement

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.cqse.check.framework.preprocessor.c.new_c_preprocessor.PreprocessorTokenReplacement
      • eu.cqse.check.framework.preprocessor.c.new_c_preprocessor.PreprocessorConditionalTokenReplacement

  • public class PreprocessorConditionalTokenReplacement
extends PreprocessorTokenReplacement
    Replacement for a conditional token (#if/#elif/#else/#endif). Contains the token of the previous region (e.g., the #if token for an #else-region replacement) for highlighting of corresponding begin/end tokens in the UI. The first directive (#if) is replaced by a normal PreprocessorTokenReplacement since it can't have a previousRegionToken.

    • Field Detail

      • previousRegionToken

        public final IToken previousRegionToken
        Link to the previous conditional directive on the same #if level as the directive replaced by this Replacement. This is null for #if directives, but set for #elif and #else directives. These links establish a chain from each #elif and #else directive to "their" #if directive.
